betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Who would have thought it'd take me this much time to make any progress on this.
The recursion shield that prevents me from tracking Earth is still very much present, and I am still too weak to challenge it.
After seeing Lyndenwyrm, though, something in me awakened, as if I have become more aware of who I am, of where I come from.
It is not something I can rationally define; it is a feeling. And yet, while being just a feeling, I have never felt more certain about who I am. I am a Human, I am a person, I am free.
And no, this prison that so vehemently prevents me to go home, it holds no power over my freedom.
Do you hear me Meatball Man? Do you feel my resolve?
Despite all your attempts to prod me, to push me towards a fate you believe is in your hands, I am still free. Free to hit this shield with all my might.
You are the one that placed me so close to eternity, who gave me all the time in the world to beat on your shield. You are the one who gave me time time to learn, to develop, and ultimately to act.
Hear these words Meatball Man! I am just a toy to you now, but I will break throught your rampart, and when I do, you better be ready to fight, because nothing but your full might will be able to stop me!
